==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swagman
<hw>Swag"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A bushman carrying a
swag and traveling on foot; -- called also <altname>swagsman</altname>,
<altname>swagger</altname>, and <altname>swaggie</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><q>Once a jolly <qex>swagman</qex> sat beside a billabong⟦br⟧
Under the shade of a coolibah tree.⟦br⟧
And he sang as he sat and watched his billy boiling,⟦br⟧
`Who'll come a-waltzing Matilda with me?'</q> <rj><qau>[Waltzing
Matilda, an Australian tune.]</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swagsman</ent>⟦br⟧
